@murong00 I've added separate guides for both Kafka source connector (this PR) and Kafka sink connector (https://github.com/apache/pulsar/pull/5210) to improve clarity, does it make sense?

And they are shown independently in the list of the built-in connector as well, so I've set different URL (.md file) for each.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/50226895/65111557-1b5daf80-da0f-11e9-9da0-a7255338a52d.png)

@stupidusername 

> But I do not understand why is this an option for source connectors.

A source connect receives messages from external system and writes them to a Pulsar topic. The "--processing-guarantees" is use for ensuring the processing guarantees for writing messages to the Pulsar topic.

@jiazhai @tuteng @Anonymitaet Can you work on clarifying the meanings for this flag?

@JamieCressey the JDBC connectors are using JDBC for talking to different database instances. It doesn't depend on any other database implementation specific logic. So ideally whether it is using an embedded SQL instance or an external one, it should work as the same.

From CI perspective, I don't think we can support running the JDBC connectors against all different type of databases. 

However it is also great to add some coverage to popular databases like MySQL or Postgres. So if you are interested in contributing test changes, you are welcome to do so.

